Joseph Olaoluwa Cadbury Nigeria Plc has announced the appointment of Mrs Kofoworola Akinkugbe and Ms Nadia Mohamed to its board as non-executive directors. According to the company’s statement obtained from the Nigerian Stock Exchange, the appointments are effective and subject to ratification at the company’s next Annual General Meeting on January 1, 2021. Akinkugbe is the founder and chief executive officer of SecureID. She also sits on the boards of the Manufacturers’ Association of Nigeria, Fintech Association of Nigeria, Sokoa Chair Centre Limited, ICS Outsourcing Limited, Lifeworth Medicare Limited, and African Missions L/Gte. Mohamed is the marketing director at Mondelez International (Africa), according to the statement. “Nadia serves as a Gerety Awards Jury member and as a non-executive director for two non-profit organisations, most notably representing Africa as a global shaper at the World Economic Forum and currently on the board of the Women’s Business Network for the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees, UNHCR, the UN Refugee Agency,” it said. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com  